1
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,760
<i>Dearest, I feel certain</i>

2
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,600
<i>that I am going mad again.</i>

3
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,960
<i>I feel we can't go</i>

4
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:35,000
<i>through another
of these terrible times,</i>

5
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,160
<i>and I... shan't</i>

6
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:40,440
<i>recover this time.</i>

7
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:44,800
<i>I begin to hear voices,
and can't concentrate.</i>

8
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,840
<i>So, I am doing
what seems to be</i>

9
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,800
<i>the best thing to do.</i>

10
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,760
<i>You have given me</i>

11
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,560
<i>the greatest possible
happiness.</i>

12
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:14,040
<i>You have been in every way</i>

13
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:16,320
<i>all that anyone could be.</i>

14
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,840
<i>I know
that I am spoiling your life,</i>

15
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:25,480
<i>and without me,
you could work.</i>

16
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,520
<i>And you will,</i>

17
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,400
<i>I know.</i>

18
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:35,640
<i>You see, I can't
even write this properly.</i>

19
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:40,480
<i>What I want to say
is that I owe</i>

20
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:43,120
<i>all the happiness
of my life to you.</i>

21
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:46,040
<i>You have been entirely patient
with me...</i>

22
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,400
<i>and</i>

23
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:52,120
<i>incredibly good.</i>

24
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:53,400
<i>Everything's gone</i>

25
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:56,040
<i>from me but the certainty</i>

26
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:58,560
<i>of your goodness.</i>

27
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:01,360
<i>I can't go on
spoiling your life any longer.</i>

28
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:07,080
<i>I don't think two people
could have been happier</i>

29
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:09,520
<i>than we have been.</i>

30
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,080
<i>Virginia.</i>

31
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,280
Good morning, Doctor.

32
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,720
Mr. Woolf.

33
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,840
No worse, I think.

34
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,760
I see.

35
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:13,760
The main thing is to keep her
where she is, and calm.

36
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,040
Friday, then.

37
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:40,200
Good morning, Leonard.

38
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,480
Good morning, Virginia.

39
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:42,840
How was your sleep ?

40
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:44,440
Uneventful.

41
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,160
The headaches ?

42
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:49,920
No. No headaches.

43
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,320
Doctor seemed pleased.

44
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:53,920
That's all from this morning ?

45
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,320
Yes. This young man
has submitted his manuscript.

46
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,880
I've found three errors of fact

47
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:59,800
and two spelling mistakes,

48
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:02,280
and I'm not yet on page four.

49
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,280
Have you had breakfast ?

50
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:05,360
Yes.

51
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,520
Liar.

52
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,520
Virginia, it's not
my insistence.

53
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,840
It's your own doctor's.

54
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:13,440
I'm going to send

55
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:16,800
Nelly up with some fruit
and a bun.

56
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:18,520
Right. Lunch, then.

57
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,520
Proper lunch,

58
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:22,160
husband and wife
sitting down together...

59
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,480
soup, pudding

60
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:25,240
and all.

61
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:27,520
By force if necessary.

62
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,640
Leonard, I believe
I may have a first sentence.

63
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,880
Work, then.

64
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,360
Then you must eat.

65
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,880
Mrs. Dalloway said...

66
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:52,120
she would buy the flowers...
herself.

67
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,360
<i>Mrs. Dalloway said</i>

68
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:56,560
<i>she would buy the flowers
herself.</i>

69
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,240
Sally, I think I'll buy
the flowers myself.

70
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:03,360
What ?

71
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:05,440
What flowers ?

72
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:08,120
Oh, shit. I forgot.

73
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,840
You're never going
to be a big boy

74
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,960
if you don't eat
your breakfast.

75
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,360
You're going to be
the big brother.

76
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,440
It's a very important job.

77
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,600
Happy birthday.

78
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:18,280
- Morning, honey.
- Oh, Dan.

79
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,840
Roses on your own birthday.

80
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,200
You're too much.
Really.

81
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,680
He'll eat it

82
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:24,760
now that you're here.

83
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,000
It's your birthday.

84
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,600
You shouldn't be out
buying me flowers.

85
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:30,200
Well, you were still sleeping.

86
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:31,880
So ?

87
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,800
Well, we decided
it would be better

88
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,680
if we let you sleep in
a little, didn't we ?

89
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,920
Morning, bug.

90
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,720
You need to rest, Laura.

91
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,320
You're only four months away.

92
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:44,440
Dan, don't.

93
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,920
I'm fine.

94
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,840
I'm just tired.

95
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,080
I've been telling him
he's got to eat his breakfast.

96
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:52,280
That's true.

97
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:54,000
So, it's a beautiful day.

98
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:56,320
What are you two going
to be doing with it ?

99
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,880
We've got our plans,
don't we ?

100
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,080
What plans ?

101
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,400
Hmm...

102
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:05,000
Well, it wouldn't
be much of a party,

103
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,000
would it, if I told you

104
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,080
every detail in advance ?

105
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,280
Well, I better just stop

106
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,880
asking questions then, huh ?

107
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:12,080
That the time ?

108
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:13,400
I better get going.

109
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,360
Have a good day.

110
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,440
You, too.

111
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,480
Dan, happy birthday.

112
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:21,640
Oh, thank you.

113
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:56,000
You need to finish
your breakfast.

114
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:22,680
Oh, I'm going to make a cake.

115
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,800
That's what I'm going to do.

116
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,800
I'm going to make the cake
for Daddy's birthday.

117
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:31,360
Mommy, can I help ?

118
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,720
Can I help make the cake ?

119
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,800
Of course you can, sweet pea.

120
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,160
I'm not going to do
anything without you.

121
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,200
No, of course.

122
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,920
You have to come.

123
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:46,080
Of course.

124
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,160
Well, I always wanted you

125
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,120
and everybody involved
in the actual ceremony.

126
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,840
I don't know.

127
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:52,240
Around 60.

128
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,640
Well, it will.

129
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:55,480
It'll mean so much.

130
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:56,760
The whole occasion.

131
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,760
It's the least I can do

132
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,760
to have a nice dinner
and say thank you

133
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:01,880
to everybody.

134
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,480
You've done so much for him.

135
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:04,960
Oh, I take that as a yes.

136
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:06,520
He'll be thrilled.

137
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,800
Oh, my God.

138
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:10,880
I'm thrilled.
Oh, good.

139
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,280
What if nobody comes ?

140
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:13,960
This is Clarissa Vaughan.

141
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:16,240
Yes, I am just confirming

142
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,520
that you're sending a car
to pick me up first.

143
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:19,840
Yeah.

144
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,440
- Hi, Clarissa.
- Hi, can't talk.

145
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:24,040
And then we're
going over to 679 Hudson,

146
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,920
which is at 9th and 14th.

147
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:29,480
Then you will take me uptown
and you will wait for us.

148
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,080
And it'll be over at seven.

149
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:42,720
Flowers !
What a beautiful morning.

150
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,640
Hi, Clarissa.
How are you ?

151
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,040
I'm having a party.

152
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:49,960
My friend Richard's won
the Carruthers.

153
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,360
Well, that's just terrific...

154
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,840
if I knew what it was.

155
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:57,440
It's a poetry prize
for a life's work.

156
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,240
It's the most prestigious.

157
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,680
For a poet,
it's the best you can do.

158
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:02,920
Oh, very good.

159
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,680
So, what would you like ?

160
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:06,520
The lilies are perfect.

161
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:09,560
No. Too morbid.

162
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:10,640
Hydrangeas, I think.

163
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,080
And, um...

164
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:16,040
Oh, oh, let's just have
buckets of roses.

165
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:22,400
And... I think I'm going
to take these with me.

166
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:23,200
Rodney ?

167
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,680
Okay.

168
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:25,680
Thank you.

169
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:30,040
I actually tried
to read Richard's novel.

170
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,920
You did ?

171
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:36,640
Oh, I know. It's not easy.

172
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:37,800
I know.

173
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:40,240
It did take him
ten years to write.

174
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:43,160
Maybe it just takes
another ten to read.

175
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:46,880
It's you, isn't it ?

176
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,280
What is ?

177
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,760
In the novel,
isn't it meant to be you ?

178
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:52,440
Oh, I see.

179
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,920
Yeah.

180
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,360
Sort of.

181
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,800
I mean, in a way.

182
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:58,080
You know, Richard's a writer.

183
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,360
That's what he is.

184
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:00,880
He uses things
which actually happen.

185
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,320
Yeah.

186
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:05,560
And years ago,
he and I were students.

187
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:06,680
That's true.

188
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,200
But, you know,
then he changes things.

189
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:09,040
Oh, sure.

190
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:11,160
I don't mean in a bad way.

191
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:18,720
It's more like...
he makes them his own.

192
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:30,320
A woman's whole life...

193
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:33,600
in a single day,

194
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:37,360
just one day...

195
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:40,200
and in that day,

196
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:42,160
her whole life.

197
00:16:43,760 --> 00:16:45,880
This is what we need.

198
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:47,320
Shortening...

199
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:48,000
Mrs. Dalloway, it's you.

200
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:49,320
Yes, it's me !

201
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,800
Oh... It's me.

202
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:53,040
Come in.

203
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:57,640
Richard,
it's a beautiful morning.

204
00:17:57,720 --> 00:18:01,040
How about we let in
a little more light ?

205
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:02,800
Is it still morning ?

206
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:04,680
Yes, it is.

207
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:06,840
Have I died ?

208
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:10,880
Good morning, my dear.

209
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:14,760
Any visitors ?

210
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:15,760
Yes.

211
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:16,920
Are they still here ?

212
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:18,400
No. They've gone.

213
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,240
Mm. How'd they look ?

214
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:22,200
Today ?

215
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:24,240
Sort of like black fire.

216
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:26,600
I mean, sort of light

217
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:30,000
and dark at the same time.

218
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:32,200
There was one a bit
like an electrified jellyfish.

219
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:35,520
They were singing.

220
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,040
May have been Greek.

221
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:41,000
So the ceremony is at 5:00.

222
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,280
Do you remember ?

223
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,520
And then...

224
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,880
the party is right after.

225
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,400
They did bring you breakfast,
didn't they ?

226
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:05,120
What a question. Of course.

227
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,160
Richard, you did eat it ?

228
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:07,520
Well, can you see it ?

229
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,680
Is it here ?

230
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:10,680
Any breakfast lying around ?

231
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:13,000
No, I don't see it.

232
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:14,760
Well, then I must have
eaten it, mustn't I ?

233
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,120
I suppose.

234
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,200
Does it matter ?

235
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,080
Of course, it matters.

236
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:24,400
You know what the doctors say.

237
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:33,200
Have you been skipping pills ?

238
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,520
Clarissa, I can't take this.

239
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,480
Take what ?

240
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:36,760
Having to be proud and brave

241
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:38,200
in front of everybody.

242
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,280
Oh. Honey, it's not
a performance.

243
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,360
Of course it is.

244
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:43,560
I got the prize
for my performance.

245
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:44,560
Well, that is
nonsense.

246
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,680
I got the prize for having AIDS
and going nuts

247
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:47,880
and being brave about it.

248
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:50,200
I actually got the prize
for having come through.

249
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:51,960
It's not true.

250
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:53,520
- For surviving, that's what
- It's not true.

251
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:55,000
I got the prize for.
Oh, you think they

252
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:56,120
would have given it to me
if I were healthy ?

253
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:58,080
Yes, as a matter of fact, I do.

254
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:07,680
Is it here somewhere ?

255
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:08,640
What ?

256
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,080
The prize.
I'd like to look at it.

257
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,360
No, you haven't gotten it yet.

258
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,960
It's tonight.

259
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,520
Are you sure ?

260
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,680
Um...

261
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,880
I remember
the ceremony perfectly.

262
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:29,360
I seem to have
fallen out of time.

263
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:34,880
Richard.

264
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:37,560
Richard...

265
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,280
it's a party,

266
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:41,560
and it's only a party.

267
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,720
Hmm ? Populated entirely

268
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:48,400
by people who respect
and admire you.

269
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:49,920
A small party, is it ?

270
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,560
A select party, is it ?

271
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:53,040
Your friends.

272
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,880
I thought I lost all my friends.

273
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:56,960
I thought I drove
my friends crazy.

274
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:58,960
Jesus.

275
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:01,160
Oh, Mrs. Dalloway,

276
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:05,640
always giving parties
to cover the silence.

277
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,440
Richard...

278
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:23,960
You won't need to do anything.

279
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:25,920
All you have to do is appear,

280
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:28,960
sit on the sofa.

281
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,520
And I will be there.

282
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:35,920
This is a group of people

283
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:39,640
who want to tell you
your work is going to live.

284
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:40,840
Oh, is it ?

285
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:43,760
Is my work going to live ?

286
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,920
I can't go through with it,
Clarissa.

287
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,960
Oh... Why do you say that ?

288
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,560
- I can't.
- Why ?

289
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:52,200
Because I wanted
to be a writer, that's all.

290
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:53,160
So ?

291
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:56,000
I wanted to write about it all.

292
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:58,080
Everything that happens
in a moment.

293
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:00,120
The way the flowers looked

294
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:01,840
when you carried them
in your arms.

295
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:04,120
This towel, how it... smells,
how it feels.

296
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,240
This thread.

297
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:07,800
All our feelings,

298
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:09,560
yours and mine.

299
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,560
The history of it,

300
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:13,200
who we once were.

301
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:14,960
Everything in the world.

302
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:19,360
Everything all mixed up...

303
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:22,120
like it's all mixed up now.

304
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:27,640
And I failed.

305
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:36,520
I failed.

306
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:40,280
No matter what you start with,
it ends up being so much less.

307
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:46,560
Sheer fucking pride...

308
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,160
and stupidity.

309
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:58,800
We want everything, don't we ?

310
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,240
I suppose we do.

311
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:06,360
You kissed me on a beach.

312
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:12,080
Yeah.

313
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,880
Do you remember...

314
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,360
how many years ago ?

315
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,560
Of course.

316
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:22,840
What did you want then ?

317
00:23:28,120 --> 00:23:29,840
Come closer.

318
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,320
I'm right here.

319
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:35,480
Come closer, would you, please ?

320
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:42,800
Take my hand.

321
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:49,280
Would you be angry ?

322
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,560
Would I be angry
if you didn't show up

323
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,840
at the party ?

324
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:58,080
Would you be angry if I died ?

325
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:59,320
If you died ?

326
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,640
Who is this party for ?

327
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:03,760
What do you mean, who's it for ?

328
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,600
What are you asking ?
What are you trying to say ?

329
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:07,320
I'm not trying to say anything.

330
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:08,440
Mm.

331
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,720
I'm saying...

332
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:14,720
I think I'm only staying alive
to satisfy you.

333
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:24,680
Well...

334
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:27,320
so that is what we do.

335
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,080
That is what people do.

336
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:32,760
They stay alive for each other.

337
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:33,760
And the doctors told you,

338
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,200
you-you don't need to die.

339
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:36,160
They told you that.

340
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:39,600
