Well, I...

838
00:51:33,720 --> 00:51:34,600
Out of the blue.

839
00:51:36,520 --> 00:51:38,200
I know the book is tough,
but I liked it.

840
00:51:39,440 --> 00:51:40,280
I know.

841
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:43,680
Only one thing upset me.

842
00:51:43,760 --> 00:51:44,920
What's that ?

843
00:51:44,960 --> 00:51:45,880
What upset you ?

844
00:51:47,840 --> 00:51:49,280
Well...

845
00:51:49,360 --> 00:51:52,160
that there wasn't more
about you.

846
00:51:56,760 --> 00:51:58,360
That's kind.

847
00:52:01,120 --> 00:52:02,880
I went back to Wellfleet.

848
00:52:06,200 --> 00:52:07,080
You did ?

849
00:52:07,160 --> 00:52:08,040
One day.

850
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:09,160
I didn't tell you ?

851
00:52:11,520 --> 00:52:12,880
No.

852
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:14,880
But then, I never see you.

853
00:52:16,280 --> 00:52:18,040
You remember the house.

854
00:52:18,080 --> 00:52:20,560
It's still there.

855
00:52:20,640 --> 00:52:21,600
I think you're courageous.

856
00:52:21,680 --> 00:52:24,400
Courageous ? Why ?

857
00:52:24,520 --> 00:52:26,160
To dare go visit.

858
00:52:26,240 --> 00:52:28,360
What I mean is...

859
00:52:28,440 --> 00:52:30,160
to face the fact

860
00:52:30,240 --> 00:52:34,520
that we have lost
those feelings forever.

861
00:52:37,400 --> 00:52:38,720
Shit !

862
00:52:38,800 --> 00:52:40,600
Clarissa ?

863
00:52:40,640 --> 00:52:42,800
Um...

864
00:52:42,840 --> 00:52:44,800
I don't know what's happening.

865
00:52:44,880 --> 00:52:45,760
I'm sorry.

866
00:52:45,840 --> 00:52:47,200
I seem to be in some strange

867
00:52:47,280 --> 00:52:48,720
sort of mood.

868
00:52:48,800 --> 00:52:49,720
I'm sorry.

869
00:52:49,760 --> 00:52:52,560
It's, uh, it's very rude of me.

870
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:56,840
I seem to be unraveling.

871
00:52:56,920 --> 00:52:57,840
I shouldn't have come.

872
00:52:57,920 --> 00:52:58,880
No, it's not you.

873
00:52:59,000 --> 00:52:59,720
It's not you.

874
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:02,640
It's more like having
a presentiment.

875
00:53:02,720 --> 00:53:04,200
Do you know what I'm saying ?

876
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:08,280
Oh, God,
it's probably just nerves

877
00:53:08,360 --> 00:53:10,240
about the party, you know ?

878
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:12,720
Bad hostess !

879
00:53:12,800 --> 00:53:15,320
Clarissa, what's happened ?

880
00:53:15,360 --> 00:53:17,080
Jesus !

881
00:53:17,120 --> 00:53:19,400
What is it ?!

882
00:53:19,480 --> 00:53:20,840
Oh ! Oh, God !

883
00:53:22,720 --> 00:53:25,680
Do you want me to go ?

884
00:53:25,760 --> 00:53:29,320
No, don't go ! Don't...

885
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:31,080
Don't go.

886
00:53:31,160 --> 00:53:32,920
Explain to me
why this is happening.

887
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:37,280
Don't... don't touch me.

888
00:53:37,400 --> 00:53:38,520
Jesus.

889
00:53:38,560 --> 00:53:40,640
It's better if you don't.

890
00:53:43,640 --> 00:53:46,240
It's just too much.

891
00:53:46,320 --> 00:53:49,080
You fly in from San Francisco,

892
00:53:49,160 --> 00:53:51,920
and I've been nursing Richard
for years.

893
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:54,920
And all the time,
I've held myself together...

894
00:53:55,000 --> 00:53:56,400
no problem.

895
00:53:56,560 --> 00:53:57,880
I know.

896
00:54:00,280 --> 00:54:03,720
One morning, in Wellfleet...

897
00:54:03,800 --> 00:54:08,040
you were there,
we were all there...

898
00:54:08,120 --> 00:54:10,520
I'd been sleeping with him,

899
00:54:10,600 --> 00:54:13,560
and I was out
on the back porch.

900
00:54:13,640 --> 00:54:17,360
He came out behind me,

901
00:54:17,440 --> 00:54:22,080
and he put his hand
on my shoulder.

902
00:54:22,160 --> 00:54:24,800
<i>Good morning, Mrs. Dalloway.</i>

903
00:54:28,360 --> 00:54:29,920
That's...

904
00:54:32,040 --> 00:54:33,640
That's when...

905
00:54:33,720 --> 00:54:36,400
From then on, I've...
been stuck.

906
00:54:36,480 --> 00:54:37,480
Stuck ?

907
00:54:37,560 --> 00:54:39,640
Yep.

908
00:54:40,920 --> 00:54:42,040
Yeah.

909
00:54:43,160 --> 00:54:44,960
With the name, I mean.

910
00:54:48,600 --> 00:54:50,960
And now you walk in.

911
00:54:51,040 --> 00:54:54,120
To see you

912
00:54:54,200 --> 00:54:57,520
walk in...
because I never see you.

913
00:54:57,600 --> 00:54:59,920
Look at you.

914
00:55:01,880 --> 00:55:06,200
Anyway, it doesn't matter.

915
00:55:06,280 --> 00:55:08,120
It was you he stayed with.

916
00:55:08,160 --> 00:55:09,120
It was you he lived with.

917
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:12,160
I had one summer.

918
00:55:23,240 --> 00:55:25,520
The day I left him,

919
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:31,960
I got on a train
and made my way across Europe.

920
00:55:32,040 --> 00:55:36,440
I felt free
for the first time in years.

921
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:55,280
So... tell me about
San Francisco.

922
00:55:55,360 --> 00:55:56,560
What's to tell ?

923
00:55:56,600 --> 00:56:00,120
I still teach drama
to idiots, mostly.

924
00:56:00,240 --> 00:56:01,680
They can't all be idiots.

925
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:03,840
No, no. In fact,

926
00:56:03,920 --> 00:56:06,800
I shouldn't tell
you this, but...

927
00:56:06,880 --> 00:56:08,000
I've fallen in love.

928
00:56:08,080 --> 00:56:10,120
Really ?

929
00:56:10,200 --> 00:56:12,200
Yes.

930
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:15,280
With a student.

931
00:56:15,360 --> 00:56:16,960
Exactly.

932
00:56:17,040 --> 00:56:18,880
I know.

933
00:56:18,960 --> 00:56:21,240
You think,
Am I still up for this ?

934
00:56:21,360 --> 00:56:23,160
All this intensity,
all those arguments,

935
00:56:23,280 --> 00:56:25,920
doors being slammed.

936
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:28,800
Well, you know what it's like.

937
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:31,240
Are you feeling better ?

938
00:56:33,400 --> 00:56:34,440
A little.

939
00:56:34,520 --> 00:56:36,000
Thank you.

940
00:56:40,120 --> 00:56:41,840
You think I'm ridiculous ?

941
00:56:43,800 --> 00:56:46,080
Ridiculous ?

942
00:56:46,160 --> 00:56:48,680
Fortunate, too.

943
00:57:17,560 --> 00:57:19,920
I'm going to leave you
at Mrs. Latch's.

944
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:21,840
I have to do something.

945
00:57:32,640 --> 00:57:35,080
Mommy, I don't want to go.

946
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:37,200
You have to. I'm sorry.

947
00:57:37,280 --> 00:57:39,360
I have something to do
before Daddy gets home.

948
00:58:25,160 --> 00:58:26,960
Hello.

949
00:58:27,040 --> 00:58:28,480
Hi, Mrs. Latch.

950
00:58:28,560 --> 00:58:30,120
My boy's not very happy.

951
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:33,360
Mommy, I don't want
to do this.

952
00:58:33,400 --> 00:58:35,800
I have to go, honey.

953
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:39,240
Your mommy has things
she has to do.

954
00:58:39,320 --> 00:58:40,720
Come in, I got cookies.

955
00:58:42,080 --> 00:58:43,000
Okay, baby ?

956
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:46,440
You have to be brave now.

957
00:58:47,960 --> 00:58:48,840
Don't worry now.

958
00:58:48,920 --> 00:58:50,240
It's going to be fine.

959
00:58:50,320 --> 00:58:51,240
Well...

960
00:59:08,280 --> 00:59:09,200
Honey !

961
00:59:28,600 --> 00:59:30,760
Come on. Come on, darling.

962
00:59:35,080 --> 00:59:37,400
Mommy !

963
00:59:37,440 --> 00:59:38,360
- Stop it.
- No !

964
00:59:38,400 --> 00:59:39,600
Darling, stop it.

965
00:59:39,640 --> 00:59:40,720
Mommy !

966
00:59:40,840 --> 00:59:41,840
- All right.
- Mommy !

967
00:59:41,880 --> 00:59:45,080
Mommy !

968
00:59:47,080 --> 00:59:48,040
Come on.

969
00:59:48,120 --> 00:59:49,480
Mommy !

970
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:53,000
Mommy !

971
00:59:54,200 --> 00:59:56,720
No !

972
01:01:27,560 --> 01:01:29,080
Breakfast is served

973
01:01:29,160 --> 01:01:31,000
between 7:00 and 11:00
in the Regency Room,

974
01:01:31,040 --> 01:01:32,280
and room service is available

975
01:01:32,360 --> 01:01:33,840
24 hours.

976
01:01:35,520 --> 01:01:37,040
Thank you, ma'am.

977
01:01:38,840 --> 01:01:40,600
Is there anything else
you need ?

978
01:01:40,760 --> 01:01:43,240
Yes, um...

979
01:01:43,320 --> 01:01:45,160
No.

980
01:01:45,240 --> 01:01:46,800
Not to be disturbed.

981
01:02:57,960 --> 01:03:01,400
<i>'Did it matter, then ? '
She asked herself,</i>

982
01:03:01,480 --> 01:03:03,800
<i>walking toward Bon Street.</i>

983
01:03:03,880 --> 01:03:08,960
<i>Did it matter that she must
inevitably cease completely ?</i>

984
01:03:09,040 --> 01:03:12,600
<i>All this must go on
without her.</i>

985
01:03:12,680 --> 01:03:15,720
<i>Did she resent it ?</i>

986
01:03:15,800 --> 01:03:18,640
<i>Or did it not become consoling</i>

987
01:03:18,680 --> 01:03:23,480
<i>to believe that death
ended absolutely ?</i>

988
01:03:23,560 --> 01:03:27,840
<i>It is possible to die.</i>

989
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:31,120
It is possible...

990
01:03:31,200 --> 01:03:32,560
<i>...to die.</i>

991
01:03:35,720 --> 01:03:38,520
There was a lovely coat
for Angelica at Harrod's,

992
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:40,040
then nothing for the boys.

993
01:03:40,120 --> 01:03:41,200
It seems so unfair.

994
01:03:41,280 --> 01:03:42,800
Why should Angelica
be favored ?

995
01:03:46,000 --> 01:03:47,200
Virginia ?

996
01:03:49,120 --> 01:03:51,480
Virginia ?

997
01:03:51,560 --> 01:03:52,920
Virginia !

998
01:03:55,080 --> 01:03:56,920
What are you thinking about ?

999
01:04:08,600 --> 01:04:11,560
Are you still with us ?

1000
01:04:21,120 --> 01:04:26,320
Your aunt's a very
lucky woman, Angelica...

1001
01:04:26,360 --> 01:04:28,760
because she has two lives.

1002
01:04:28,800 --> 01:04:31,160
She has the life
she's leading,

1003
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:33,720
and also the book she's writing.

1004
01:04:33,800 --> 01:04:37,880
This makes her very
fortunate indeed.

1005
01:04:37,960 --> 01:04:39,920
What were you thinking about ?

1006
01:05:05,800 --> 01:05:09,920
I was going to kill
my heroine...

1007
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:13,320
but I've changed my mind.

1008
01:05:14,680 --> 01:05:17,360
I... I can't.

1009
01:05:30,440 --> 01:05:33,840
I fear I may have to kill
someone else instead.

1010
01:05:41,160 --> 01:05:42,680
Oh, Quentin !

1011
01:05:43,960 --> 01:05:45,000
We're ready !

1012
01:05:46,600 --> 01:05:48,120
A fascinating visit.

1013
01:05:48,200 --> 01:05:51,360
We enjoyed it thoroughly.

1014
01:05:52,440 --> 01:05:53,640
Do you have to go already ?

1015
01:05:55,320 --> 01:05:56,520
I do wish you wouldn't go.

1016
01:05:56,600 --> 01:05:57,480
Oh, Virginia,

1017
01:05:57,560 --> 01:06:00,280
the last thing you want
is our noisiness.

1018
01:06:00,360 --> 01:06:03,800
My hopeless, clumsy boys.

1019
01:06:03,880 --> 01:06:05,640
Say good-bye, boys.

1020
01:06:05,720 --> 01:06:08,000
Bye !

1021
01:06:10,200 --> 01:06:11,440
You'll return to what ?

1022
01:06:11,480 --> 01:06:12,880
Tonight ?

1023
01:06:12,920 --> 01:06:18,120
Oh, just some...
insufferable dinner.

1024
01:06:18,200 --> 01:06:21,040
Not even you could
envy, Virginia.

1025
01:06:21,120 --> 01:06:22,520
But I do.

1026
01:06:58,040 --> 01:06:59,280
Say something, Nessa.

1027
01:06:59,320 --> 01:07:00,920
Didn't you think
I seemed better ?

1028
01:07:01,080 --> 01:07:03,240
Yes...

1029
01:07:03,320 --> 01:07:06,640
Yes... Virginia,
you seemed better.

1030
01:07:19,880 --> 01:07:21,360
You think...

1031
01:07:22,520 --> 01:07:25,680
You think I may one day escape ?

1032
01:07:25,720 --> 01:07:28,840
One day. One...

1033
01:07:30,480 --> 01:07:31,400
Nessa.

1034
01:07:33,720 --> 01:07:34,960
Nessa !

1035
01:07:35,000 --> 01:07:36,560
Come on, Nessa.

1036
01:07:36,600 --> 01:07:38,160
Come, Angelica, we must go.

1037
01:07:40,280 --> 01:07:41,560
Come on !

1038
01:07:41,600 --> 01:07:42,520
Good-bye.

1039
01:07:42,560 --> 01:07:44,560
Good-bye, little girl.

1040
01:07:44,640 --> 01:07:47,240
Angelica !

1041
01:07:47,320 --> 01:07:48,640
The train !

1042
01:07:50,680 --> 01:07:53,360
We're going to miss the train.

1043
01:07:53,400 --> 01:07:54,840
Come on. Hurry up.

1044
01:07:54,920 --> 01:07:55,840
Big step.

1045
01:08:01,000 --> 01:08:02,480
Come on, come on, come on !

1046
01:08:02,560 --> 01:08:04,080
I want to go home.

1047
01:08:04,120 --> 01:08:05,040
Yeah, all right.

1048
01:08:05,080 --> 01:08:07,400
We stayed too long,
we've missed the train.

1049
01:08:07,480 --> 01:08:09,560
Stay close.

1050
01:09:29,560 --> 01:09:31,040
I'm sorry, I know.

1051
01:09:31,120 --> 01:09:32,440
I tried to get here earlier.

1052
01:09:32,480 --> 01:09:34,000
I tried, okay ? Don't start.

1053
01:09:34,040 --> 01:09:35,840
I know,

1054
01:09:35,920 --> 01:09:39,520
it's just incredibly important
because it's your party.

1055
01:09:39,600 --> 01:09:42,080
Julia, how have you been doing ?

1056
01:09:42,200 --> 01:09:44,560
I'm fine.

1057
01:09:44,600 --> 01:09:45,400
Come here.

1058
01:09:45,440 --> 01:09:48,160
What have you been doing ?

1059
01:09:48,240 --> 01:09:50,520
Well, studying, Mom.

1060
01:09:54,280 --> 01:09:55,320
Um...

1061
01:09:55,400 --> 01:09:58,240
So, what should I do ? Chairs ?

1062
01:09:58,320 --> 01:10:00,480
No. Let's clear off the desk
first.

1063
01:10:00,560 --> 01:10:03,360
You can take it
into the bedroom.

1064
01:10:03,440 --> 01:10:05,720
I bumped into Louis Waters.

1065
01:10:05,760 --> 01:10:07,000
Oh, you did ?

1066
01:10:07,040 --> 01:10:08,200
Where ?

1067
01:10:08,280 --> 01:10:09,160
In the street.

1068
01:10:12,120 --> 01:10:13,560
They're all here, aren't they ?

1069
01:10:13,640 --> 01:10:14,640
All the ghosts.

1070
01:10:14,800 --> 01:10:18,360
All of the ghosts are
assembling for the party.

1071
01:10:18,400 --> 01:10:21,080
He's so weird.

1072
01:10:21,120 --> 01:10:23,520
Oh, what ?

1073
01:10:23,600 --> 01:10:24,840
You can't see that ?

1074
01:10:24,920 --> 01:10:27,280
You can't see that
Louis Waters is weird ?

1075
01:10:30,000 --> 01:10:31,880
I can see that he's sad.

1076
01:10:31,960 --> 01:10:36,200
Well... all your friends
are sad.

1077
01:10:38,440 --> 01:10:40,160
You've been crying.
What's happening ?

1078
01:10:44,160 --> 01:10:46,240
All it is,
I looked around this room,

1079
01:10:46,320 --> 01:10:49,040
<i>and I thought,
I'm giving a party.</i>

1080
01:10:49,080 --> 01:10:51,600
<i>All I want to do
is give a party.</i>

1081
01:10:51,640 --> 01:10:52,880
And ?

1082
01:10:52,920 --> 01:10:55,640
I know why he does it;
he does it deliberately.

1083
01:10:55,720 --> 01:10:58,560
Oh, is this Richard ?

1084
01:10:58,640 --> 01:11:00,080
Of course.

1085
01:11:00,120 --> 01:11:01,840
He did it this morning.

1086
01:11:01,880 --> 01:11:03,800
He gives me that look.

1087
01:11:03,880 --> 01:11:05,240
What look ?

1088
01:11:06,520 --> 01:11:08,760
To say...

1089
01:11:08,800 --> 01:11:12,480
<i>Your life is... trivial.</i>

1090
01:11:13,480 --> 01:11:16,400
<i>You are so trivial.</i>

1091
01:11:16,440 --> 01:11:18,800
Just...

1092
01:11:18,840 --> 01:11:20,320
daily stuff, you know.

1093
01:11:20,400 --> 01:11:22,680
Schedules and parties
and... details.

1094
01:11:22,760 --> 01:11:26,400
That's what he means... by it,
that is what he's saying.

1095
01:11:26,480 --> 01:11:28,560
Mom, it only matters
if you think it's true.

1096
01:11:30,240 --> 01:11:31,760
Well ?

1097
01:11:31,800 --> 01:11:33,680
Do you ? Tell me.

1098
01:11:36,440 --> 01:11:38,720
When I'm with him, I feel...

1099
01:11:42,640 --> 01:11:44,960
Yes, I am living.

1100
01:11:46,680 --> 01:11:50,040
And when I'm not with him...

1101
01:11:50,120 --> 01:11:52,600
Yes, everything does seem
sort of s...

1102
01:11:52,680 --> 01:11:54,880
...silly.

1103
01:11:59,800 --> 01:12:01,520
I don't mean with you.

1104
01:12:01,560 --> 01:12:02,760
Oh, I...

1105
01:12:02,840 --> 01:12:05,480
God. Jesus.

1106
01:12:06,720 --> 01:12:08,640
Never with you.

1107
01:12:08,720 --> 01:12:09,760
It's all the rest of it.

1108
01:12:14,840 --> 01:12:16,040
Sally ?

1109
01:12:17,240 --> 01:12:19,000
The rest of it.

1110
01:12:23,280 --> 01:12:25,840
False comfort.

1111
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:27,360
Because ?

1112
01:12:28,480 --> 01:12:30,360
<i>If you say to me,
When were you happiest ?</i>

1113
01:12:30,400 --> 01:12:31,520
Mom...

1114
01:12:31,600 --> 01:12:34,000
<i>Tell me the moment
you were happiest.</i>

1115
01:12:34,080 --> 01:12:37,120
I know, I know,
it was years ago.

1116
01:12:37,200 --> 01:12:40,120
Yeah.

1117
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:44,560
All you're saying is...
you were once young.

1118
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:53,000
I remember one morning...

1119
01:12:53,080 --> 01:12:55,040
getting up at dawn,

1120
01:12:55,120 --> 01:12:59,240
there was such a sense
of possibility.

1121
01:12:59,320 --> 01:13:01,160
You know ?
That feeling ?

1122
01:13:01,240 --> 01:13:02,240
Hmm ?

1123
01:13:02,320 --> 01:13:04,560
And I remember
thinking to myself,

1124
01:13:04,600 --> 01:13:07,400
<i>So, this is the
beginning of happiness.</i>

1125
01:13:07,480 --> 01:13:09,200
<i>This is where it starts.</i>

1126
01:13:09,280 --> 01:13:12,240
<i>And, of course, there
will always be more.</i>

1127
01:13:15,640 --> 01:13:18,040
It never occurred to me

1128
01:13:18,120 --> 01:13:21,040
it wasn't the beginning.

1129
01:13:22,680 --> 01:13:25,840
It was happiness.

1130
01:13:25,880 --> 01:13:31,360
It was the moment...

1131
01:13:31,440 --> 01:13:33,560
right then.

1132
01:14:55,160 --> 01:14:56,960
Ah, Nelly, good evening.
I was wondering

1133
01:14:57,080 --> 01:14:58,120
if you'd seen Mrs. Woolf.

1134
01:14:58,200 --> 01:15:00,080
I thought you knew, sir.

1135
01:15:00,160 --> 01:15:02,080
Mrs. Woolf has gone out.

1136
01:15:37,360 --> 01:15:38,720
Excuse me ! Excuse me !

1137
01:16:04,680 --> 01:16:06,880
Mr. Woolf, what an
unexpected pleasure.

1138
01:16:06,960 --> 01:16:08,400
Perhaps you could tell me

1139
01:16:08,480 --> 01:16:10,560
exactly what you think
you're doing ?

1140
01:16:10,600 --> 01:16:11,920
What I was doing ?

1141
01:16:12,000 --> 01:16:13,240
I went to look for you,
and you weren't there.

1142
01:16:13,320 --> 01:16:15,760
You were working in the garden.
I didn't wish to disturb you.

1143
01:16:15,840 --> 01:16:17,480
You disturb me
when you disappear.

1144
01:16:17,560 --> 01:16:18,480
I didn't disappear.

1145
01:16:20,360 --> 01:16:21,600
I went for a walk.

1146
01:16:21,640 --> 01:16:23,160
A walk ?!
Is that all ?

1147
01:16:23,240 --> 01:16:24,800
Just a walk ?

1148
01:16:26,120 --> 01:16:28,560
Virginia, we must go home now.
Nelly's cooking dinner.

1149
01:16:28,640 --> 01:16:30,960
She's already had
a very difficult day.

1150
01:16:31,080 --> 01:16:32,720
It's just our obligation
to eat Nelly's dinner.

1151
01:16:32,800 --> 01:16:35,040
There is no such
obligation.

1152
01:16:35,120 --> 01:16:37,320
No such obligation exists.

1153
01:16:37,400 --> 01:16:38,360
Virginia,

1154
01:16:38,440 --> 01:16:39,920
you have an obligation
to your own sanity.

1155
01:16:40,000 --> 01:16:42,000
I have endured this custody !

1156
01:16:42,080 --> 01:16:44,400
I have endured
this imprisonment.

1157
01:16:44,520 --> 01:16:45,720
Oh, Virginia !

1158
01:16:45,800 --> 01:16:48,400
I am attended by
doctors, everywhere.

1159
01:16:48,480 --> 01:16:50,240
I am attended by doctors

1160
01:16:50,320 --> 01:16:52,800
who inform me of
my own interests !

1161
01:16:52,880 --> 01:16:54,000
They know your interests.

1162
01:16:54,080 --> 01:16:55,040
They do not !

1163
01:16:55,120 --> 01:16:56,880
They do not speak
for my interests.

1164
01:16:56,960 --> 01:16:58,200
Virginia, I can...

1165
01:16:58,280 --> 01:17:00,560
I can see that it must be
hard for a woman of your...

1166
01:17:00,640 --> 01:17:02,400
- Of what ? Of my what, exactly ?
- Uh, your...

1167
01:17:02,440 --> 01:17:03,480
your talents to see

1168
01:17:03,560 --> 01:17:05,400
that she may not be
the best judge

1169
01:17:05,480 --> 01:17:06,600
of her own condition !

1170
01:17:06,680 --> 01:17:08,600
Who, then, is a better judge ?

1171
01:17:08,680 --> 01:17:09,880
You have a history !

1172
01:17:11,400 --> 01:17:13,200
You have a history
of confinement.

1173
01:17:13,280 --> 01:17:14,680
We brought you to Richmond

1174
01:17:14,760 --> 01:17:17,640
because you have a history
of fits, moods, blackouts,

1175
01:17:17,720 --> 01:17:19,160
hearing voices.

1176
01:17:19,240 --> 01:17:21,120
We brought you here

1177
01:17:21,160 --> 01:17:22,560
to save you
from the irrevocable damage

1178
01:17:22,600 --> 01:17:25,680
you intended upon yourself.

1179
01:17:25,760 --> 01:17:28,320
You've tried to kill yourself
twice !

1180
01:17:32,080 --> 01:17:33,480
I live daily with that threat.

1181
01:17:33,560 --> 01:17:35,920
I set up the press...
we set up the printing press

1182
01:17:36,000 --> 01:17:37,960
not just for itself,

1183
01:17:38,040 --> 01:17:41,200
not just purely for itself,
but so that you might have

1184
01:17:41,280 --> 01:17:44,560
a ready source
of absorption and of remedy.

1185
01:17:44,640 --> 01:17:45,800
Like needlework ?

1186
01:17:46,840 --> 01:17:48,960
It was done for you !

1187
01:17:49,040 --> 01:17:51,200
It was done for your betterment !

1188
01:17:51,280 --> 01:17:53,240
It was done out of love !

1189
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:58,680
If I didn't know you better,
I'd call this ingratitude.

1190
01:17:58,760 --> 01:18:01,600
I am ungrateful ?

1191
01:18:01,680 --> 01:18:03,760
You call me ungrateful ?

1192
01:18:05,480 --> 01:18:08,880
My life has been stolen from me.

1193
01:18:11,480 --> 01:18:14,400
I'm living in a town
I have no wish to live in.

1194
01:18:14,480 --> 01:18:18,920
I'm living... a life
I have no wish to live.

1195
01:18:22,720 --> 01:18:25,400
How did this happen ?

1196
01:18:37,960 --> 01:18:41,200
It is time for us
to move back to London.

1197
01:18:46,480 --> 01:18:48,640
I miss London.

1198
01:18:48,680 --> 01:18:51,640
I miss London life.

1199
01:18:54,240 --> 01:18:56,200
This is not you speaking,
Virginia.

1200
01:18:56,280 --> 01:18:57,680
This is an aspect
of your illness.

1201
01:18:57,760 --> 01:18:59,640
- It's not you.
- It is me. It is my voice.

1202
01:18:59,760 --> 01:19:00,720
It's not your voice.

1203
01:19:00,800 --> 01:19:01,960
It's mine and mine alone.

1204
01:19:02,040 --> 01:19:03,400
This is the voice
that you hear.

1205
01:19:03,480 --> 01:19:06,080
It is not ! It is mine !

1206
01:19:06,120 --> 01:19:08,040
I'm dying in this town !

1207
01:19:12,040 --> 01:19:13,920
If you were thinking clearly,
Virginia,

1208
01:19:13,960 --> 01:19:15,240
you'd recall it was London

1209
01:19:15,320 --> 01:19:16,920
that brought you low.

1210
01:19:17,000 --> 01:19:19,760
If I were thinking clearly...

1211
01:19:20,840 --> 01:19:23,480
If I were thinking clearly...

1212
01:19:23,560 --> 01:19:26,160
We brought you to Richmond
to give you peace.

1213
01:19:26,240 --> 01:19:28,960
If I were thinking clearly,
Leonard,

1214
01:19:29,000 --> 01:19:32,840
I would tell you that I wrestle
alone in the dark,

1215
01:19:32,920 --> 01:19:36,000
in the deep dark,
and that only I can know,

1216
01:19:36,080 --> 01:19:38,960
only I can understand
my own condition.

1217
01:19:40,280 --> 01:19:41,800
You live with the threat...
you tell me...

1218
01:19:41,960 --> 01:19:43,680
you live with the threat
of my extinction.

1219
01:19:45,080 --> 01:19:47,160
Leonard, I live with it,

1220
01:19:47,240 --> 01:19:48,680
too.

1221
01:19:52,200 --> 01:19:54,720
This is my right.

1222
01:19:54,760 --> 01:19:56,960
It is the right
of every human being.

1223
01:19:57,040 --> 01:20:00,440
I choose not the suffocating
anesthetic of the suburbs,

1224
01:20:00,520 --> 01:20:02,680
but the violent jolt
of the capital.

1225
01:20:02,760 --> 01:20:04,440
That is my choice.

1226
01:20:04,520 --> 01:20:06,960
The meanest patient,

1227
01:20:07,040 --> 01:20:09,560
yes, even the very lowest
is allowed some say

1228
01:20:09,640 --> 01:20:12,160
in the matter of her own
prescription.

1229
01:20:12,240 --> 01:20:14,480
Thereby she defines
her humanity.

1230
01:20:22,880 --> 01:20:25,600
I wish, for your sake, Leonard,

1231
01:20:25,640 --> 01:20:31,000
I could be happy in this
quietness.

1232
01:20:31,080 --> 01:20:36,200
But if it is a choice between
Richmond and death,

1233
01:20:36,280 --> 01:20:37,920
I choose death.

1234
01:20:48,200 --> 01:20:50,240
Very well, London, then.

1235
01:20:51,600 --> 01:20:53,720
We'll go back to London.

1236
01:21:27,000 --> 01:21:29,840
You hungry ?

1237
01:21:34,440 --> 01:21:36,440
I'm a little hungry myself.

1238
01:21:55,400 --> 01:21:58,360
Come along.

1239
01:21:58,440 --> 01:22:00,440
London train on platform one !

1240
01:22:00,520 --> 01:22:04,520
This is the London train
terminating at Vauxhall.

1241
01:22:08,840 --> 01:22:13,360
You cannot find peace
by avoiding life, Leonard.

1242
01:22:21,120 --> 01:22:23,040
This is the London train !

1243
01:22:24,400 --> 01:22:28,040
London train on platform one !

1244
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:47,960
Mommy !

1245
01:22:57,320 --> 01:22:58,960
Hey. Hey, there, bug.

1246
01:22:59,040 --> 01:23:00,960
Hey, what's wrong ?

1247
01:23:01,040 --> 01:23:02,720
Hi, Mrs. Latch.

1248
01:23:02,760 --> 01:23:03,840
Sorry I'm late.

1249
01:23:03,920 --> 01:23:04,920
He's fine.

1250
01:23:05,000 --> 01:23:05,920
He's been fine.

1251
01:23:05,960 --> 01:23:07,400
He's, he's just happy
to see you.

1252
01:23:07,480 --> 01:23:09,680
Aw, it couldn't have been
that bad, could it ? Hmm ?

1253
01:23:09,760 --> 01:23:11,360
So, you got it cut, then ?

1254
01:23:11,400 --> 01:23:13,240
Oh, yes, yes. No problem.

1255
01:23:13,280 --> 01:23:14,160
Looks great.

1256
01:23:14,240 --> 01:23:15,600
Well, they didn't have
to do very much.

1257
01:23:15,680 --> 01:23:17,280
Well, we had a fine time

1258
01:23:17,320 --> 01:23:18,600
together.

1259
01:23:19,680 --> 01:23:21,560
Thank you very much.

1260
01:23:25,680 --> 01:23:29,360
So, that wasn't too bad, was it ?

1261
01:23:29,440 --> 01:23:30,920
I wasn't gone too long.

1262
01:23:31,000 --> 01:23:33,000
No, you weren't long.

1263
01:23:33,080 --> 01:23:34,800
That's right.

1264
01:23:37,480 --> 01:23:40,160
At one point...

1265
01:23:40,200 --> 01:23:42,120
I don't know.

1266
01:23:44,960 --> 01:23:49,480
There was a moment where
I thought I might be longer.

1267
01:23:49,560 --> 01:23:51,280
But I changed my mind.

1268
01:23:58,760 --> 01:23:59,680
What is it, honey ?

1269
01:23:59,720 --> 01:24:03,120
Mommy, I love you.

1270
01:24:05,240 --> 01:24:07,240
I love you, too, baby.

1271
01:24:15,400 --> 01:24:17,120
What's wrong ?

1272
01:24:20,760 --> 01:24:21,760
What ?

1273
01:24:29,160 --> 01:24:30,560
Don't worry, honey,
everything's fine.

1274
01:24:30,600 --> 01:24:33,280
We're going to have
a wonderful party,

1275
01:24:33,320 --> 01:24:37,000
and we've made your daddy
such a nice cake.

1276
01:24:42,440 --> 01:24:43,920
I love you, sweetheart.

1277
01:24:45,160 --> 01:24:47,360
You're my guy.

1278
01:25:22,640 --> 01:25:27,400
Mommy !

1279
01:26:21,560 --> 01:26:24,440
Richard, it's me. I'm early.

1280
01:26:28,840 --> 01:26:30,880
What the hell is going on ?

1281
01:26:31,840 --> 01:26:32,760
Richard !

1282
01:26:35,840 --> 01:26:37,840
What are you doing here ?
You're early !

1283
01:26:37,920 --> 01:26:40,080
Wha-What is going on here ?

1284
01:26:40,160 --> 01:26:41,720
What are you doing ?

1285
01:26:41,760 --> 01:26:43,520
I- I had this wonderful idea.

1286
01:26:43,560 --> 01:26:46,720
I needed some light.
I needed to let in some light !

1287
01:26:46,760 --> 01:26:49,360
Richard, what are you doing ?

1288
01:26:49,440 --> 01:26:51,680
I had this fantastic notion.

1289
01:26:51,720 --> 01:26:53,880
I took the Xanax
and the Ritalin together.

1290
01:26:53,960 --> 01:26:55,360
It-it never occurred to me.

1291
01:26:55,400 --> 01:26:56,040
Richard...

1292
01:26:56,120 --> 01:26:57,160
Don't come near me !

1293
01:27:01,720 --> 01:27:07,280
It seemed to me I needed
to let in some light.

1294
01:27:09,080 --> 01:27:12,880
What do you think ?
I cleared away all the windows.

1295
01:27:12,960 --> 01:27:15,440
All right, Richard,
do me one simple favor.

1296
01:27:15,560 --> 01:27:16,600
Come. Come sit.

1297
01:27:16,680 --> 01:27:19,480
I don't think I can make it
to the party, Clarissa.

1298
01:27:19,560 --> 01:27:20,600
You don't have to go
to the party.

1299
01:27:20,680 --> 01:27:21,880
You don't have to go
to the ceremony.

1300
01:27:21,920 --> 01:27:23,520
You don't have to do anything
you don't want to do.

1301
01:27:23,560 --> 01:27:25,040
You can do as you like.

1302
01:27:25,160 --> 01:27:28,000
But I still have to face
the hours, don't I ?

1303
01:27:28,080 --> 01:27:30,080
I mean, the hours
after the party,

1304
01:27:30,160 --> 01:27:32,320
and the hours after that...

1305
01:27:32,360 --> 01:27:35,320
You do have good days still.

1306
01:27:35,360 --> 01:27:37,080
You know you do.

1307
01:27:37,160 --> 01:27:39,360
Not really.

1308
01:27:39,400 --> 01:27:42,200
I mean, it's kind of you
to say so, but it's...

1309
01:27:42,240 --> 01:27:43,520
not really true.

1310
01:27:51,960 --> 01:27:52,880
Are they here ?

1311
01:27:52,960 --> 01:27:54,640
Who ?

1312
01:27:54,720 --> 01:27:55,440
The voices.

1313
01:27:55,520 --> 01:27:58,240
Oh, the voices are always here.

1314
01:27:58,280 --> 01:28:01,880
And it's the voices that you're
hearing now, isn't it ?

1315
01:28:01,960 --> 01:28:03,600
No, no, no, no.

1316
01:28:03,680 --> 01:28:06,920
Mrs. Dalloway, it's you.

1317
01:28:11,400 --> 01:28:14,800
I've stayed alive for you,

1318
01:28:14,880 --> 01:28:16,640
but now you have to let me go.

1319
01:28:18,400 --> 01:28:19,320
Richard, I...

1320
01:28:19,400 --> 01:28:20,360
No, wait, wait, wait, wait.

1321
01:28:20,440 --> 01:28:22,600
Wait.

1322
01:28:26,280 --> 01:28:27,200
Tell me a story.

1323
01:28:27,240 --> 01:28:28,800
What about ?

1324
01:28:28,880 --> 01:28:32,640
Tell me a story from your day.

1325
01:28:32,720 --> 01:28:33,640
I, um...

1326
01:28:33,720 --> 01:28:35,560
I- I got up...

1327
01:28:35,640 --> 01:28:37,200
Yes ?

1328
01:28:37,280 --> 01:28:43,480
...and I went out, and, uh,
I went to buy flowers,

1329
01:28:43,520 --> 01:28:45,360
Like Mrs. Dalloway,
in the book, you know ?

1330
01:28:45,440 --> 01:28:46,760
Yes.

1331
01:28:46,840 --> 01:28:47,840
And it was a beautiful morning.

1332
01:28:47,920 --> 01:28:49,320
Was it ?

1333
01:28:49,400 --> 01:28:51,320
Yes, it was so beautiful.

1334
01:28:51,400 --> 01:28:53,000
It was so fresh.

1335
01:28:53,080 --> 01:28:54,720
Oh, fresh, was it ?

1336
01:28:54,800 --> 01:28:55,760
Yes.

1337
01:28:59,440 --> 01:28:59,960
Like a...

1338
01:29:01,640 --> 01:29:02,680
like a morning on the beach ?

1339
01:29:02,720 --> 01:29:04,240
Yes.

1340
01:29:04,320 --> 01:29:05,360
Like that ?

1341
01:29:05,440 --> 01:29:07,200
Yes.

1342
01:29:07,240 --> 01:29:11,000
Like that morning when you
walked out of that old house,

1343
01:29:11,080 --> 01:29:14,120
and you were, you were 18,
and maybe I was 19.

1344
01:29:14,200 --> 01:29:15,920
Yes.

1345
01:29:16,000 --> 01:29:18,040
I was 19 years old,

1346
01:29:18,080 --> 01:29:22,480
and I'd never seen
anything so beautiful.

1347
01:29:23,560 --> 01:29:24,520
You...

1348
01:29:24,600 --> 01:29:26,400
coming out of a glass door

1349
01:29:26,440 --> 01:29:28,880
in the early morning,
still sleepy.

1350
01:29:28,960 --> 01:29:31,640
Isn't it strange ?

1351
01:29:32,880 --> 01:29:37,360
Most ordinary morning
in anybody's life.

1352
01:29:39,800 --> 01:29:42,680
I'm afraid I can't make it
to the party, Clarissa.

1353
01:29:42,760 --> 01:29:46,040
The party...

1354
01:29:46,160 --> 01:29:48,040
doesn't matter.

1355
01:29:48,120 --> 01:29:51,440
You've been so good to me,
Mrs. Dalloway.

1356
01:29:53,600 --> 01:29:55,600
I love you.

1357
01:30:00,600 --> 01:30:02,000
<i>I don't think two people</i>

1358
01:30:02,080 --> 01:30:04,360
<i>could've been happier
than we've been.</i>

1359
01:30:12,000 --> 01:30:13,040
Oh, God, no !

1360
01:30:21,840 --> 01:30:23,800
Happy birthday.

1361
01:30:23,880 --> 01:30:25,120
Happy birthday, Dan.

1362
01:30:25,160 --> 01:30:26,400
This is perfect.

1363
01:30:26,480 --> 01:30:28,160
This is just perfect.

1364
01:30:28,200 --> 01:30:30,320
Oh, do you think so ?

1365
01:30:30,400 --> 01:30:31,440
Do you really think so ?

1366
01:30:31,520 --> 01:30:32,400
Why, sure.

1367
01:30:32,480 --> 01:30:34,200
You must've been
working all day.

1368
01:30:34,240 --> 01:30:35,880
Well, that's what
we were doing.

1369
01:30:36,000 --> 01:30:37,520
Weren't we, bug ?

1370
01:30:37,600 --> 01:30:39,680
Been working all day.

1371
01:30:39,720 --> 01:30:40,840
This is just fantastic.

1372
01:30:40,920 --> 01:30:42,360
It's what I've always wanted.

1373
01:30:42,440 --> 01:30:44,120
Oh, Dan.

1374
01:30:44,200 --> 01:30:45,480
One day, Richie, I'll tell you.

1375
01:30:45,560 --> 01:30:47,200
I'll tell you
how it all happened.

1376
01:30:47,240 --> 01:30:49,120
Don't.

1377
01:30:49,160 --> 01:30:50,240
I want to.

1378
01:30:50,320 --> 01:30:53,120
I want to tell him the story.

1379
01:30:53,200 --> 01:30:54,120
What happened...

1380
01:30:54,200 --> 01:30:55,720
when I was in the war.

1381
01:30:55,800 --> 01:30:58,200
At war, I found myself

1382
01:30:58,240 --> 01:31:00,360
thinking about this girl
that I had seen...

1383
01:31:00,440 --> 01:31:01,760
I had never met her...

1384
01:31:01,840 --> 01:31:03,080
at high school,

1385
01:31:03,160 --> 01:31:04,600
this... strange,

1386
01:31:04,680 --> 01:31:08,560
fragile-looking girl
named Laura McGrath.

1387
01:31:11,920 --> 01:31:13,160
Yeah.

1388
01:31:13,240 --> 01:31:14,240
And she was shy...

1389
01:31:15,280 --> 01:31:17,760
and she was interesting.

1390
01:31:17,840 --> 01:31:20,120
And... well,
your mother won't mind if

1391
01:31:20,160 --> 01:31:21,080
I tell you this, Richie.

1392
01:31:21,120 --> 01:31:22,600
She was the sort of
girl that you see

1393
01:31:22,680 --> 01:31:23,680
sitting mostly on her own.

1394
01:31:23,760 --> 01:31:25,400
And I'll tell you...

1395
01:31:25,480 --> 01:31:27,880
sometimes, when I was
in the South Pacific,

1396
01:31:27,960 --> 01:31:29,560
the fact is

1397
01:31:29,600 --> 01:31:30,880
that I used to think

1398
01:31:30,960 --> 01:31:32,440
about this girl.

1399
01:31:32,560 --> 01:31:33,440
Dan.

1400
01:31:33,520 --> 01:31:34,880
I used to think

1401
01:31:34,920 --> 01:31:36,800
about bringing her to a house,

1402
01:31:36,840 --> 01:31:39,040
to a life.

1403
01:31:40,240 --> 01:31:42,080
Pretty much like this.

1404
01:31:43,760 --> 01:31:46,200
And it was the thought
of the happiness...

1405
01:31:47,800 --> 01:31:51,080
the thought of this woman,

1406
01:31:51,160 --> 01:31:52,200
the thought of this life...

1407
01:31:52,280 --> 01:31:53,960
that's what kept me going.

1408
01:31:55,400 --> 01:31:57,760
I had an idea of our happiness.

1409
01:32:24,640 --> 01:32:26,480
Why does someone have to die ?

1410
01:32:30,640 --> 01:32:31,880
Leonard...

1411
01:32:31,960 --> 01:32:33,600
In your book,
you said someone had to die.

1412
01:32:33,680 --> 01:32:34,560
Hmm.

1413
01:32:34,640 --> 01:32:36,640
Why ?

1414
01:32:38,240 --> 01:32:41,040
Is that a stupid question ?

1415
01:32:41,120 --> 01:32:42,400
No.

1416
01:32:42,480 --> 01:32:43,760
I imagine my question is stupid.

1417
01:32:45,520 --> 01:32:47,400
Not at all.

1418
01:32:48,720 --> 01:32:49,920
Well ?

1419
01:32:52,560 --> 01:32:54,440
Someone has to die

1420
01:32:54,520 --> 01:32:57,080
in order that the rest of us
should value life more.

1421
01:32:59,120 --> 01:33:00,960
It's contrast.

1422
01:33:01,040 --> 01:33:03,120
And who will die ?

1423
01:33:04,880 --> 01:33:06,400
Tell me.

1424
01:33:09,000 --> 01:33:11,960
The poet will die.

1425
01:33:12,000 --> 01:33:14,600
The visionary.

1426
01:33:28,240 --> 01:33:29,440
What are you doing ?

1427
01:33:29,560 --> 01:33:31,680
I'm brushing my teeth.

1428
01:33:35,880 --> 01:33:37,760
Are you coming to bed ?

1429
01:33:37,840 --> 01:33:40,280
Yeah, in a minute.

1430
01:33:42,240 --> 01:33:44,480
Come to bed, Laura Brown.

1431
01:33:48,800 --> 01:33:50,240
I ran into Ray.

1432
01:33:50,280 --> 01:33:52,200
He said Kitty had to
go to the hospital.

1433
01:33:53,760 --> 01:33:55,680
I know.

1434
01:33:55,760 --> 01:33:56,960
Nothing serious.

1435
01:33:57,000 --> 01:33:59,120
He said just a checkup.

1436
01:34:00,640 --> 01:34:02,560
I'm terrified.

1437
01:34:02,640 --> 01:34:04,600
Why ?

1438
01:34:06,800 --> 01:34:09,120
Only I knew
that she could disappear.

1439
01:34:11,040 --> 01:34:12,160
Maybe you could

1440
01:34:12,240 --> 01:34:13,920
go see her
in the morning, honey.

1441
01:34:21,520 --> 01:34:22,920
I was going to.

1442
01:34:23,000 --> 01:34:25,600
I was going to stop by.

1443
01:34:25,640 --> 01:34:28,320
I've had a wonderful day,

1444
01:34:28,400 --> 01:34:30,800
and I have you to thank.

1445
01:34:36,120 --> 01:34:40,320
Come to bed, honey.

1446
01:34:40,360 --> 01:34:42,360
I'm coming.

1447
01:34:50,640 --> 01:34:53,480
Are you coming ?

1448
01:34:53,560 --> 01:34:55,400
Yes.

1449
01:35:13,160 --> 01:35:15,120
What ?

1450
01:35:18,080 --> 01:35:20,240
I was hoping
you were going to bed.

1451
01:35:20,320 --> 01:35:22,320
I am.

1452
01:35:22,400 --> 01:35:24,280
I am going to bed.

1453
01:35:26,600 --> 01:35:28,480
What, then ?

1454
01:35:30,600 --> 01:35:33,640
All else is clear.

1455
01:35:33,720 --> 01:35:36,320
The outline of the story
is planned,

1456
01:35:36,400 --> 01:35:38,120
now one thing only.

1457
01:35:38,200 --> 01:35:40,960
Mrs. Dalloway's destiny
must be resolved.

1458
01:36:20,720 --> 01:36:23,400
You're Laura Brown.

1459
01:36:23,480 --> 01:36:28,120
Yes, I'm Richard's mother.

1460
01:36:30,080 --> 01:36:32,120
Of course.

1461
01:36:34,120 --> 01:36:35,560
I'm Clarissa Vaughan.

1462
01:36:35,640 --> 01:36:37,360
Please come in.

1463
01:36:45,880 --> 01:36:48,640
My friend Sally
is in the kitchen,

1464
01:36:48,720 --> 01:36:50,960
and my daughter.

1465
01:36:51,040 --> 01:36:52,800
I'll take this.

1466
01:36:52,920 --> 01:36:55,680
We were having a party.

1467
01:36:55,720 --> 01:36:58,920
We were going to have a party.

1468
01:36:59,000 --> 01:37:00,160
I was lucky.

1469
01:37:00,240 --> 01:37:01,920
I got the last plane
from Toronto.

1470
01:37:01,960 --> 01:37:06,360
So, that's the monster.

1471
01:37:06,440 --> 01:37:08,520
Hope I did the right thing.

1472
01:37:08,600 --> 01:37:10,480
I found your number
in his phone book.

1473
01:37:10,560 --> 01:37:14,760
Yes, he had it.

1474
01:37:14,840 --> 01:37:17,240
We didn't speak often.

1475
01:37:28,640 --> 01:37:31,880
It's a terrible thing,
Miss Vaughan... to outlive

1476
01:37:31,960 --> 01:37:33,520
your whole family.

1477
01:37:36,920 --> 01:37:39,320
Richard's father died.

1478
01:37:39,400 --> 01:37:42,680
Yes, he-he died of cancer
quite young.

1479
01:37:42,720 --> 01:37:44,560
And Richard's sister is dead.

1480
01:37:50,080 --> 01:37:53,040
Obviously, you...
feel unworthy.

1481
01:37:53,120 --> 01:37:57,880
Gives you feelings
of unworthiness.

1482
01:37:57,960 --> 01:38:01,000
You survive and they don't.

1483
01:38:05,240 --> 01:38:07,360
Have you read the poems ?

1484
01:38:07,440 --> 01:38:09,840
Oh, yes. Oh...

1485
01:38:11,440 --> 01:38:13,400
I also read the novel.

1486
01:38:20,800 --> 01:38:25,680
You see, uh, people say
the novel is difficult.

1487
01:38:25,760 --> 01:38:29,280
Uh... I know.

1488
01:38:29,360 --> 01:38:31,160
They say that.

1489
01:38:35,920 --> 01:38:38,360
I know.

1490
01:38:40,520 --> 01:38:43,040
He had me die in the novel.

1491
01:38:43,120 --> 01:38:45,680
I- I-I know why he did that.

1492
01:38:50,440 --> 01:38:51,480
It hurt, of course.

1493
01:38:51,520 --> 01:38:53,760
I can't pretend it didn't hurt,
but I...

1494
01:38:53,800 --> 01:38:57,160
I know why he did it.

1495
01:38:59,760 --> 01:39:03,760
You left Richard
when he was a child.

1496
01:39:05,480 --> 01:39:09,600
I left both my children.

1497
01:39:09,640 --> 01:39:12,240
I abandoned them.

1498
01:39:18,000 --> 01:39:21,480
They say it's the worst thing
a mother can do.

1499
01:39:34,080 --> 01:39:35,640
You have a daughter.

1500
01:39:38,880 --> 01:39:41,560
Yes...

1501
01:39:41,600 --> 01:39:44,440
But I never met Julia's father.

1502
01:39:44,520 --> 01:39:46,600
You so wanted a child.

1503
01:39:48,360 --> 01:39:50,880
That's right.

1504
01:39:50,960 --> 01:39:53,800
You're a lucky woman.

1505
01:40:02,720 --> 01:40:05,240
There are times
when you don't belong,

1506
01:40:05,280 --> 01:40:08,240
and you think you're going
to kill yourself.

1507
01:40:14,480 --> 01:40:16,600
Once, I went to a hotel.

1508
01:40:20,200 --> 01:40:23,680
Later that night, I made a plan.

1509
01:40:23,760 --> 01:40:26,120
The plan was
I would leave my family

1510
01:40:26,200 --> 01:40:30,240
when my second child was born...

1511
01:40:30,280 --> 01:40:32,680
and that's what I did.

1512
01:40:32,760 --> 01:40:36,360
I got up one morning,

1513
01:40:36,440 --> 01:40:38,840
made breakfast,

1514
01:40:38,920 --> 01:40:42,240
went to the bus stop,

1515
01:40:42,280 --> 01:40:45,360
got on a bus.

1516
01:40:45,440 --> 01:40:47,600
I'd left a note.

1517
01:40:51,720 --> 01:40:56,280
I got a job in a library
in Canada.

1518
01:41:02,600 --> 01:41:04,440
It would...

1519
01:41:06,400 --> 01:41:10,120
be wonderful to say
you regretted it.

1520
01:41:10,200 --> 01:41:12,120
It would be easy.

1521
01:41:17,080 --> 01:41:19,720
But what does it mean ?

1522
01:41:19,800 --> 01:41:23,640
What does it mean to regret...

1523
01:41:23,720 --> 01:41:26,480
when you have no choice ?

1524
01:41:36,480 --> 01:41:38,800
It's what you can bear.

1525
01:41:44,400 --> 01:41:46,240
There it is.

1526
01:41:46,360 --> 01:41:48,600
No one's going to forgive me.

1527
01:41:54,640 --> 01:41:58,600
It was death.

1528
01:41:58,680 --> 01:42:01,280
I chose life.

1529
01:42:58,600 --> 01:43:01,120
Time to take your coat off.

1530
01:43:43,280 --> 01:43:45,240
I thought you might like
a cup of tea.

1531
01:43:45,280 --> 01:43:46,920
Oh my goodness.

1532
01:43:47,000 --> 01:43:48,760
Thank you, dear.

1533
01:43:48,800 --> 01:43:50,840
I feel like I'm stealing
your room.

1534
01:43:52,800 --> 01:43:53,760
Um, we put the food away,

1535
01:43:53,880 --> 01:43:55,600
so, if you're at all hungry
in the night,

1536
01:43:55,680 --> 01:43:56,760
just help yourself.

1537
01:43:56,800 --> 01:43:57,960
Oh, I will.

1538
01:43:58,040 --> 01:44:00,080
Where will you sleep ?

1539
01:44:00,160 --> 01:44:01,400
Oh, the sofa.

1540
01:44:01,440 --> 01:44:03,280
Oh, oh, I'm sorry.

1541
01:44:11,000 --> 01:44:13,160
Good night, sweetheart.

1542
01:44:14,360 --> 01:44:16,240
Good night.

1543
01:44:35,200 --> 01:44:37,200
<i>Dear Leonard,</i>

1544
01:44:37,280 --> 01:44:42,240
<i>to look life in the face...</i>

1545
01:44:42,320 --> 01:44:48,320
<i>always to look life in the face,</i>

1546
01:44:48,360 --> 01:44:53,600
<i>and to know it for what it is.</i>

1547
01:44:53,680 --> 01:44:59,000
<i>At last, to know it,</i>

1548
01:44:59,040 --> 01:45:02,600
<i>to love it for what it is,</i>

1549
01:45:02,680 --> 01:45:06,160
<i>and then...</i>

1550
01:45:06,240 --> 01:45:08,840
<i>to put it away.</i>

1551
01:45:12,440 --> 01:45:15,640
<i>Leonard...</i>

1552
01:45:15,680 --> 01:45:20,120
<i>always the years between us,</i>

1553
01:45:20,160 --> 01:45:23,760
<i>always the years...</i>

1554
01:45:23,840 --> 01:45:28,960
<i>always... the love...</i>

1555
01:45:29,000 --> 01:45:32,160
<i>always...</i>

1556
01:45:32,240 --> 01:45:34,560
<i>the hours.</i>

